{
  "text": "Nonchaotic behaviour in 3D quadratic systems Proof. Note that systems (7.1)-(7.8), (7.10), (7.11)+, and (7.12)-(7.21) all have at least one monotone component which hence has a limit as t \u2192 \u221e. The scalar form of (7.9) is ... zz \u2213 z 2 \u2212 z 3\u017c \u2212z\u017c = 0 which can be directly integrated. System (7.11)\u2212 can be written as\u1e8b = (\u1e8f x ) [CITATION_1] ",
